Name: Description
COVID-19 Cases: Cases data represent the total cumulative number of confirmed cases since the start of the outbreak, by place of residence. Rates are calculated using interpolated intercensal population estimates updated in 2019 by the Department of Health, and represent the rate per 100,000 people.

Name: Source Notes
COVID-19 Cases:
New York City Department of Health and Mental Hygiene, COVID-19 Data (2020). Retrieved from: https://github.com/nychealth/coronavirus-data

Data are updated weekly.

Name: Notes
COVID-19 Cases: <normal>Data are cumulative and do not represent new cases per day listed. Data are being collected in real-time and are preliminary and subject to change as COVID-19 response continues. Due to delays in reporting, recent data are incomplete. Zip code data does not include cases where resident zip code is unknown. </normal>
